OL,5, As sentient waves crush battered seas  
OL,6, Lampooned sorry maids churn cries      
OL,7, Of merked sense and salty vines        
OL,8, Woe! Must the vast rays seek revenge?  
OL,9, I must sense them at once!             
OL,10, Cursed marry mathered twains, and set  
OL,11, Goshed parry men seen entrhalled       
OL,12, Overseeing the giant tradition lies    
OL,13, A hefty vet, cheetah make-up like      
OL,14, His presidential claims button me      
OL,15, As I clasp shut my praying hands       
OL,16, "Lo, lacker sherh, mend dit culpatt! @@
OL,17, I have seen famine like no other, but  
OL,18, see my regret in provition of comfort!"
OL,19, That night was a gathering of virtual  
OL,20, mess, a stealing company of the turt   
